Question for you: Does your partner support your health habits?
👫💖👭💖👬
That's the topic this week on my blog (LINK IN PROFILE).
🍫🍩🎂🍦🍰
What do you do when your partner doesn't support your health habits?
🥝🥒🏊🏼‍♀️🤸🏽‍♀️🥗
This is a question that comes up time and time again.
🙌🏼😫😕🍲
When we change our lifestyle - including our #diet, personal care products, #homecleaning products, #kitchen #cookware and equipment, bedding, and many other elements that contribute to a healthy home, it isn't just us that's affected. It's our #partners, #children, parents, #friends and other #family members. No person is an island 🌴 - and the choices we make ripple and spread outward.
🙌🏼👫👬👭🙌🏼
So is there anything you can do if your partner doesn't support your health habits?
🙋🏻
While you can't change people or convince them to bend to your will, there are ways you can address this issue with your partner to create more harmony in your home 🏡.
💛💛💛
LINK IN PROFILE or visit undiet.me/healthandlove to get my tips on how to negotiate this topic with your loved ones (or perhaps just #tag them in this post!!!)
📷: @catherine_farquharson

I traveled to Sayulita Mexico with @zyrken and @frostifresh to shoot a freerunning and lifestyle video for @nlymancom It was such a chill and much needed escape from my daily  routine. We stayed in this gorgeous house a mile and a half hike out of the main town that over looked the ocean with an infinity pool. I got to surf everyday and explore this beach side city of Mexico. Oddly enough I had ran into a couple fans who lived local and was able to have a beach session with them on a tire that had been dug into the sand. Travel is one of my greatest passions and being surround with positive like minded people made it even better.
